  "riddle": "1. Seek the trail of a leader who took her position as a representative of autonomy on a significant day in the year 2019. When did she begin her term?\n\n2. A post formed to steer New Caledonia's governance arose in the late 1990s. Can you uncover the year it began its journey?\n\n3. Before you proceed, look up how far above the sea the office holding this position stands. What is its elevation?\n\n4. Libraries house knowledge. Count how many stand within reach of this governmental seat. \n\n5. Now, take the elevation you found in clue 3 and combine it with the count of libraries from clue 4. What is the absolute difference?\n\n6. The path of autonomy is defined by agreements. Calculate the number of days between May 28, 1999, and March 15, 2026. How many days is that?\n\n7. Another institution plays a distinct role in the political landscape. Investigate how high this governance framework rises above sea level. What elevation do you discover?\n\n8. The years between key events shape the future. Calculate the number of days from May 28, 1999, to March 15, 2026, once more. \n\n9. A different timeline also exists: measure the days between July 10, 2004, and March 15, 2026. What’s the count you arrive at?\n\n10. From your findings in clue 9, sum the digits of the result. What total do you find?\n\n11. Turn your attention to a governing body entrusted with representing the people. How many seats populate this chamber?\n\n12. Elevation tells tales of position. Ascertain how high the seat of governance is located. What number do you find?\n\n13. Houses of worship dot the landscape. Seek out how many churches lie in proximity to the governing body’s seat.\n\n14. To move forward, you must determine the absolute difference between the elevation found in clue 12 and the number of churches you discovered in clue 13. What is that value?\n\n15. Focus on the assembly's reach; find the number of 1-bits in the binary representation of the total seats from clue 11. How many do you count?\n\n16. At last: compute the result of combining the discoveries from clues 4 and 13 with this formula: (clue 4 + clue 13) % 10. What single digit emerges from this calculation?",
